  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 5.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Sanctify...  yourselves;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "הִתְקַדְּשׁוּ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Note the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "absence",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of any such direction in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 15:11-14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with our note on ver. 12 in particular. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The filthiness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "אֶת־הַגְּדִּה",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This word occurs twenty-seven times, and is rendered \"separation\" fifteen times, \"flowers\" twice, \"put apart\" three times, \"uncleanness\" or \"filthiness\" six times, and \"menstruous\" once. The term, therefore, is among the strongest that could be used, and glances probably at the abominations, of whatsoever sort, that Ahaz's idolatries had entailed (comp. ver. 16). 2 Chronicles 29:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hezekiah gathered the priests and Levites together \"into the open space of the east,\" i.e., in the eastern open space before the temple, not \"in the inner court\" (Berth.), - see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 10:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " -and called upon them (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") to sanctify themselves, and then to sanctify the house of the Lord. To purify the temple they must first sanctify themselves (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), in order to proceed to the work of sanctifying the house of God in a state of Levitical purity. The work was to remove all that was unclean from the sanctuary. הנּדּה is Levitical uncleanness, for which in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we have הטּמאה; here the abominations of idolatry. The king gave the reason of his summons in a reference to the devastation which Ahaz and his contemporaries had wrought in the house of God (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and to the wrath of God which had on that account come upon them (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). \"Our fathers\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), that is, Ahaz and his contemporaries, for only these had been guilty of displeasing God in the ways mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"have turned away their face from the dwelling of Jahve, and turned their back (upon it).\" These words are a symbolical expression for: they have ceased to worship Jahve in His temple, and exchanged it for idolatry.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]